<br>
-Yes twinking does give you an advantage for the lower levels<br>
<br>
-Yes this will allow even poor players to level fast<br>
<br>
-Yes the danger can be a development of bad habits <br>
<br>
-Yes the majority of crap Monks I have seen are twinked alts that get hauled out of the closet and dusted off every few months<br>
<br>
However........ <br>
<br>
-I have researched my class online and off and have a good intellectual understanding of how to play it<br>
<br>
- I learn something new or increase my skills every time I log on<br>
<br>
-I have taken to heart some of the outstanding advise I have been kindly given by some of the best Monks on our server (and by observing what NOT to do from the worst) <br>
<br>
-Good gear will only take you so far and you will stagnate and die if you dont have the skills to match your gear by frustration and a bad reputation when you continuously screw up on a simple pull or split or poor aggro management etc  (and we all agree I am sure that a good reputation &gt; all things)<br>
<br>
-It allows you to quickly advance beyond what to me are the boring lower level to better enjoy the better things the game has to offer <br>
<br>
Most twinks dont get past 20 or 30, those that do rarely get past 40 and only a very small percentage make it to 50 let alone take it all the way to 60 so how does this affect you guys again except for a bit of equipment envy???....<br>
<br>
I am so very lucky to have a husband who has a level 60 character and that he was able to twink both my Monk and a Druid.<br>
<br>
I am also very fortunate that it has allowed me to begin to learn and respect two completely different classes and make an informed decision as to my main character (my druid is for porting my friends around and to focus on trade skills when I get tired of pull kill pull kill rinse repeat). It has also allowed me the flexibility of grouping and soloing and that allows me to decide my own play times <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Lets not hate twinks cause they have better gear etc lets make an informed decision based on how well they play their class as my husband was NEVER twinked or power levelled and I am so  very proud of his skills that he has learned and shared with me.<br>
<br>
He may not be the best Gravelord this server has ever seen (Xarr and Roggel and Tristran etc spring to mind) and many gravelords have better gear than he (though he has been well cared for by his guild in that respect) and he may have many many MANY faults but I have never heard of anyone that has ever said that he didnt play his class to the best of his ability and that he wasnt an asset to their group or raid. <br>
<br>
With him as my mentor and friend and husband helping me be the best I can be I would hope that people would look past me being twinked and take me for who I am, how I interact in the game and my skills in my own right.<br>
<br>
Warm Regards,<br>
<br>
Trehuga Hippykrap Druid of the 34th Season<br>
Mronk Bonesmasher Humble Monk of the 48th Circle<br>
<br>
p.s. I feel the utmost respect for those who have had to &quot;do it tough&quot; like my hubbie had to so please lets not misconstrue my post as being elitist or ignorant or full of my self <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
